rComments: Very hard to sit through his lectures, which is unfortunate because missing them is a must not. Examinations were difficult.

Everyone told me the course is easy. It is easy IF you are able to memorize a bunch of songs and are able to identify them when they're played in random order. The professor is okay in the sense that he explains stuff well but is somewhat boring to listen to. Attending classwatching weboption is a must.
Extremely hard professor. Do not take this course unless you really enjoy music theory. Even if you enjoy music, if you do not enjoy the theory behind it you will have a miserable time.
Hard to get a good mark

He seems laid back, and smiles like he cares about students - WRONG. Unrealistic expectations on exams, ambiguous instructions for assignments. He doesn't answer emails and is usually too busy to meet in office hours. Prof didn't even show up to the final exam! I fought for my A-. Avoid this prof, trust me!
